The '''Reborn Masters''' were originally members of [[Desann]]'s [[Reborn]] force, but after its downfall the survivors went on to serve [[Tavion Axmis]]. They were amongst the highest ranking members of both the original Reborn group and Tavion's [[Disciples of Ragnos]] organization. Clad in heavy purple body armor they wielded long [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsabers]] similar to that used by their former master Desann. While most of the masters used single lightsabers, several had been noted employing dual sabers and [[Double-bladed lightsaber/Legends|saberstaffs]].

Reborn Masters were extremely skilled [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]] Force-users and excellent lightsaber duelists, able to overcome an average [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]]. They could also use [[Light side of the Force/Legends|light side]] Force powers such as [[Force healing/Legends|Force heal]], [[Force barrier/Legends|Force protection]] and [[Tutaminis|Force absorb]]. To complete their abilities, Reborn Masters also utilized [[Dun Möch/Legends|Dun Möch]] in combat to weaken their opponents' resolve.

Unlike the standard [[Sith cultist/Legends|cultists]], masters rarely participated in cult missions unless they were of the highest importance. Two masters were dispatched to [[Taspir III]] to ensure that the Jedi would not rescue [[Rosh Penin]], whom the cult were holding captive after Penin's attempt to flee them. [[Jaden Korr]] engaged and defeated both masters after encountering them as he searched for Rosh. Two more masters were also present during the [[Battle of Korriban (Disciples of Ragnos crisis)|Battle of Korriban]]. They stalled the Jedi in the [[Valley of the Dark Lords/Legends|Valley of the Dark Lords]] until they were engaged and defeated by Korr. Apart from these notable ventures, the Reborn Masters remained a very quiet and secretive part of the cult.

==Behind the scenes==
In ''[[Star Wars: Jedi Knight: Jedi Academy]]'' game, during the Battle of Korriban, the player comes across a staff-wielding Reborn Master who is able to best three Jedi Knights with ease. This, however, is a scripted event and not representative for this fighter's actual in-game skills: As soon as the player activates a certain trigger, the three Jedi's hitpoints drop from 200 to 1, thereby allowing their opponent to finish them off with a single, insignificant hit, whereas the Reborn Master remains in "Undying-mode" until attacked by Jaden himself.

